<h1 align="center">Treasure Hunter Game</h1>

<p align="center">
  A puzzle-based game built with a C backend and a Python interface
</p>

---

## Overview

Treasure Hunter is a puzzle-based game that generates maps and challenges players to locate hidden treasure.  
The project integrates a low-level C backend with a Python frontend, demonstrating cross-language interaction and modular system design.

---

## Features

- Procedurally generated puzzle maps  
- Integration between Python and compiled C libraries  
- Modular separation between game logic and interface  
- Configurable settings via `.ini` and JSON files  
- Automated build process using Make  

---

## Project Structure

```bash
A3-main/
│── c/              # Core game logic (C)
│── python/         # Game interface (Python)
│── assets/         # Configuration and data files
│── dist/           # Compiled shared libraries
│── Makefile
│── env.sh
│── README.md
```

---

## Getting Started

### 1. Set up environment

```bash
source env.sh
```

### 2. Build the project

```bash
make
```

### 3. Run the game

```bash
python3 python/run_game.py
```

---

## Technical Highlights

- Cross-language integration between C and Python  
- Memory management and modular design in C  
- Build automation using Makefiles  
- Separation of concerns between backend and interface  

---

## Notes

- The shared libraries in `dist/` are required to run the game  
- These can be rebuilt using the provided Makefile  

---

